==English==
===Noun===
'''pectin'''
{{wikipedia}}

#A substance extracted from the [[cell wall]]s of plants, especially of fruits; under [[acidic]] conditions it forms a [[gel]].  It is often used in processed foods, especially [[jelly|jellies]] and [[jam]]s where it causes thickening ([[setting]]).
#:''Apple is rich in '''pectin''' and so is often added to other fruits when making jam so it will set.''